er" having the longest run\line of them all. He backstabbed Bob Burman's PC after they together killed off an outdoor (cavern) encounter.\line \line Burman's last words petitioned Odin (of all patrons) and I proceeded to roll like 3 100's in a row to verify and analyze t
he extent to which Odin might react. This was followed by several high 90's rolls.\line \line James knew something was up when I rolled the first 100 in front of them both, but then I took Bob to a secluded spot (out of sight, but not hearing range of James) where I
 continued rolling the great rolls, which sent Burman into spasms, while laughing and pounding his head against the wall (I kid you not!) while James reacted to Burman (he called it "Burmania") by screaming from the kitchen as I witnessed the head-banging:
 "Fudge! Fudgin' Judgin'!!\line \line That's the strangest PC killing PC event I've witnessed, and let me tell you, it was enough! }}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://piedpiperpublishing.yuku.com/topic/1988" }{\fldrslt \*\cs8\cf2\ul\ulc0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f1\fs24\lang1033\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033{\cf3\ul\ulc0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f3\fs20\lang1025\loch\f3\fs20\lang1025 [RJK] http://piedpiperpublishing.yuku.com/topic/1988}}}}
