\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af1\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af1\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang1033\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f3\fs20\lang1025\loch\f3\fs20\lang1025 Luck. Well that's a long story of "turn around is fair play."\line \line Robilar was trapped in GH Castle, as a 3rd level, He had run from a wight who'd come out behind him\line forward, unfortunately, into an unmapped cell area. Another wight came out in front of him. W
ell...\line Just then EGG's former wife flung open the door to Gary's study where we were playing and started screaming about how much of waste it had been over the past weeks of playing this game, and other not so nice interjections to the point where EGG was 
given a head-ache. He looked at me, knowing full well that I would never survive two wights, picked up a die and said: "If it's a 1 or 2, this has all been a dream." He tossed the die: "2". Mary Gygax didn't know it then, but she inadvertently saved Robila
r.\line \line In the Dark Druids adventure I returned the favor for Jim Ward, who had lost _everything_. We were at my old house on Madison Street (two houses down from where Gary now lives today, in fact) and everything had gone wrong for Jim, mostly because of his
 unrelenting greedy attitude, but also due to the toughness of the adventure. I handed him the die, told him the Robilar story, and said, "On a 1 or 2, this has been a dream. And you get to throw it at least." He rubbed it between his mitts making all kind
s of ritualistic gyrations and blew on it, and with a yelp hurled it upwards where it impacted with the ceiling and then fell to the floor: "2".\line \line And so was Bombadil saved by the Goddess of Luck, who I always assumed had worked through Mary Gygax... : ) }}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://piedpiperpublishing.yuku.com/topic/1994" }{\fldrslt \*\cs8\cf2\ul\ulc0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f1\fs24\lang1033\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033{\cf3\ul\ulc0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f3\fs20\lang1025\loch\f3\fs20\lang1025 [R
