\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af1\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af1\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang1033\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f3\fs20\lang1025\loch\f3\fs20\lang1025 Fact is that I have run OD&D games every year at several cons for the last five or so years. I start them at 2nd level and use the old dungeon levels. So far about eight parties have been taken out by some kobolds on the 1st level. New RPGers seem to have 
not learned to run away when in doubt.\line \line The first to fall used a sleep spell to get eight of the kobolds, but the six remaining ones used javelins to kill two PCs, then closed and in hand-to-hand killed all but two or the remainder of the party. One was ab
out to kill another PC, while a second charged the m-u of the group, who turned to flee, finally. Too late, a javelin got him. Each group that died thus added to the kobolds:\line \line 1st TPK brought 12 more kobolds\line 2nd TPK gave them armor class of 6\line 3rd (near) TP
K gave them all +1 HP\line 4th TPK added +1 damage\line 5th TPK added 4 2nd level and 2 3rd level kobolds\line 6th TPK gave them tactical manouvering and a 4th level leader\line 7th TPK upped AC to 5\line 8th TPK gave them unshakable morale\line \line At JanCon this year the Old Guard Kobol
ds joined battle with a group of 8 PCs and wiped them out. I haven't decided how that will add to their combat ability, but I am considreing a kobold shaman with at least two 1st level spells }}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://piedpiperpublishing.yuku.com/topic/2280?page=2" }{\fldrslt \*\cs8\cf2\ul\ulc0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f1\fs24\lang1033\loch\f1\fs24\lang1033{\cf1\ul\ulc0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f3\fs20\lang1025\loch\f3\fs20\lang1025 [EGG] http://piedpiperpublishing.yuku.com/topic/2280?page=2}}}}
